headline: 3 Healthcare Stocks We Approach with Caution
summary: From novel pharmaceuticals to telemedicine, most healthcare companies are on a mission to drive better patient outcomes. But speed bumps such as inventory destockings have persisted in the wake of COVID-19, limiting growth. This has capped returns as the industry’s six-month gain of 7.5% has lagged the S&P 500’s 13% climb.
